ong conference that examined the relationship between security and the environment the event brought together political scientists physicists historians biologists and others from across the university and focused on how climate change might affect political stability the role of international agreements in protecting the environment food security and freshwater ocean and other resource conflicts the goal of the event said cisac co director mariano florentino cuellar was to start a dialogue about the potential relationships between security and the environment with the expectation that it would lead to future research projects and collaborations and ultimately to policy recommendations in addition to cuellar participants included woods co directors jeffrey r koseff and barton h thompson david holloway katherine d marvel kenneth a schultz david lobell kaitlin shilling meg caldwell lynn eden toshihiro higuchi and walter p falcon search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest program on food security and the environment to build a global education network on agriculture and the environment july 29 2010 fsi stanford fse news fsi's new program on food security and the environment tackles global hunger and environmental destruction april 1 2006 fsi stanford fse news fse researchers study on climate change and hunger published in science february 4 2008 fsi stanford fse in the news cesp senior fellows receive funding from the presidential fund to support the launch of the new program on food security and the environment february 8 2006 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4920 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
